"SHADOW JAB"

Shadow Jab
Class ability: Shade
Debuff type: Stealth

Your Jab ability causes a debuff equal to your Charisma divided by 5 (rounded
up) to your victim's dodge, for 15 seconds. This effect may stack.

See also: JAB
#
"SHADOW KICK"

Shadow Kick
Class ability:  Assassin
Debuff type:  Battle

Your Kick ability causes a penalty to physical and magical damage equal to
your total level divided by 50 for 10 seconds.

See also: KICK
#
SHADOWCAGE "SHADOW CAGE"

Shadowcage
Class ability: Occultist
Debuff type: Stealth
Cost: 50 move
Cooldown: 30 seconds
Usage:  shadowcage

You create a cage of shadows, penalizing all enemies. The first victim loses
dodge equal to 4x your Charisma. Each additional victim loses dodge equal to 2x
Charisma instead. This effect lasts 15 seconds.
#
SHADOWSTEP "SHADOW STEP"

Shadowstep (Stealth ability)

Usage:  shadowstep <target>
Cooldown:  1 minute
Cost:  50 move

Shadowstep allows a talented assassin to step into one shadow and, seemingly,
appear out of another. This ability takes you instantly to your target. It has
a maximum range of 7 map tiles and requires Infiltrate if you don't have per-
mission to enter your target's location.

Players in the room you leave will not notice your departure, but players at
your destination will notice your arrival.

You cannot shadowstep to NPCs that belong to other empires, or that are on land
that belongs to other empires.

Gains experience when you use Shadowstep.

See also: INFILTRATE
#
SNEAK SNEAKING

Sneak (Stealth ability)

Usage:  sneak <direction>

Used for sneaking (moving in and out of rooms without anyone taking notice). 
When you type sneak, there is no way to know if you're actually sneaking. It's
based on your skill, and how well other people notice you.

At a high enough Stealth level, this ability will always succeed.

Gains experience when you try to sneak.

See also: HIDE
#
"STAGGER JAB"

Stagger Jab
Class ability: Powerbroker
Debuff type: Stealth

Your Jab ability causes a debuff equal to your Charisma divided by 5 (rounded
up) to your victim's to-hit, for 15 seconds. This effect may stack.

See also: JAB
#
STEAL STEALING

Steal (Stealth ability)

Usage:  steal [item]

To steal from an empire, at least one of their members must be online. This
will immediately trigger a state of "distrust" if you aren't already in one.
There is a chance the other empire will be alerted to your location. You'll
be marked internally as hostile for 1 hour, and become a valid PVP target. If
you die, any items stolen in the last 30 minutes will be left on your corpse.

This ability has two functions:

With Steal, you can pick up items from rooms that are claimed by other empires.
You do this with the "get" command. You can't steal from allies or people you
have a non-aggression pact with.

You can also steal stored resources. If you type "steal" in a storage room or
building, it will list what you can steal there. Type "steal <item>" to take
one.

Gains experience when you steal something.

See also: VAULTCRACKING
#
"SUMMON THUG"

Usage:  summon thug
Cooldown:  30 seconds
Cost:  50 move

This ability summons a local thug who will stand around and distract whoever
is following you. This is best combined with the Disguise ability, as you can
mask yourself as a thug. Thugs will have the empire of the tile they are
summoned on.

Gains experience when you attempt to summon thugs.

See also: DISGUISE
#
TERRIFY

Terrify (Stealth ability)

Usage:  terrify [victim]
Cooldown:  15 seconds
Duration:  30 seconds
Debuff type:  Stealth
Cost:  15 move

Use the power of the shadows to make your foes cower in fear, lowering the
physical and magical damage they deal by an amount equal to your total level
divided by 30. This ability has a chance of success based on your Stealth level.

Gains experience when you try to terrify someone.
#
"UNSEEN PASSING"

Unseen Passing (Stealth ability)

When in a city or indoors, Unseen Passing makes you immune to the "where" and
"track" commands. It doesn't work in the wilderness or in adventures.

This ability gains experience whenever it prevents you from being found with
"where", and whenever it prevents you from leaving tracks.

See also: NO TRACE, WHERE, TRACK
#
VAULTCRACKING "VAULT CRACKING"

Vaultcracking (Stealth ability)

This ability allows you to use the "steal" command in vaults and secret caches.

Gains experience when you steal something which requires the 'withdraw' empire
privilege (generally from the vault or secret cache).

See also: STEAL
#
WHISPERSTRIDE

Whisperstride
Class ability: Assassin, Bandit, Powerbroker, Smuggler
Usage:  whisperstride
Cooldown:  5 minutes
Cost:  100 move
Duration:  30 seconds

Whisperstride allows you to surround yourself with unnatural whispering sounds,
making your normal movement act as sneaking for a short time. You can still be
seen in the room unless you hide.

You cannot use Whisperstride while mounted.

See also: SNEAK
